    <h1>Why tortoise has a broken shell</h1>
  </div>
<p>There was a time when tortoise had a very shiny shell and was very speedy. He loved to race around and show off to the disdain of many who had their normal routines interferred with by tortoise. One day tortoise discovered that the birds were having a feast in the heavens, and wanted to be included too. The cunning tortoise talked to the birds and persuaded them to make him some wings. Being the generous creatures that they were, each bird contributed a feather and glued them together, fixing them into tortoise's arm sockets. After several trials, and with the wind in his favour, tortoise was able to fly and he raced up through the clouds leaving the birds far behind. When he arrived at the feast, tortoise ate all the food. This made the birds angry and they plucked off his feathers. He fell from the skies and landed with all his weight centered on his shell thus breaking it into hundreds of pieces. Although the animals tried to piece tortoise's shell back together, he would never move speedily again.</p>

    

